---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { siteBase } from "../lib/site";

const title = "COMPASS: Build Intuition. Trust the Reading.";
const description =
  "A 6-week live programme for tarot, oracle, and Lenormand readers who want to move beyond meanings and learn how to trust the reading.";
const ogUrl = new URL("/compass/", siteBase(Astro)).href;
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} ogUrl={ogUrl} tdcPlacement="none">
  <article class="compass page-inner">
    <h1 class="compass__h1">COMPASS: Build Intuition. Trust the Reading.</h1>

    <p class="compass__p">
      You already know the cards. That is not the problem.
    </p>

    <p class="compass__p">
      The problem is what happens when you’re in the middle of a reading. You see something, then hesitate. You feel a clear thread, then second-guess it. You start explaining instead of interpreting. You reach for meanings instead of staying with what is actually unfolding.
    </p>

    <p class="compass__p">
      COMPASS exists to change that.
    </p>

    <section class="compass__section">
      <h2 class="compass__h2">If This Sounds Like You</h2>
      <ul class="compass__list">
        <li>You know the meanings, but your readings still feel uncertain</li>
        <li>You start strong, then lose the thread halfway through</li>
        <li>You over-explain instead of saying what you actually see</li>
        <li>You feel intuitive hits, then immediately doubt them</li>
        <li>
          You keep looking for the “right” meaning instead of trusting your read
        </li>
        <li>
          You finish readings and think: that wasn’t as clear as it should have been
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="compass__section">
      <h2 class="compass__h2">What You’ll Learn</h2>
      <p class="compass__p">
        Most tarot training focuses on what the cards mean.
      </p>
      <p class="compass__p">
        COMPASS focuses on what the reader is doing.
      </p>
      <p class="compass__p">
        You will learn how to trust your own perception in a reading, stay with it, and communicate it clearly.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="compass__section">
      <h2 class="compass__h2">The COMPASS Method</h2>
      <ul class="compass__list">
        <li>Center</li>
        <li>Open</li>
        <li>Map</li>
        <li>Perceive</li>
        <li>Align</li>
        <li>Sense</li>
        <li>Seal</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="compass__p">
        This is not about learning more tarot. It is about learning how to read.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="compass__section">
      <h2 class="compass__h2">How It Works</h2>
      <p class="compass__p">
        This is a 6-week live programme for a small group of readers.
      </p>
      <ul class="compass__list">
        <li>Weekly live sessions</li>
        <li>Guided practice readings</li>
        <li>Direct feedback and correction</li>
        <li>Real application, not theory</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="compass__section">
      <h2 class="compass__h2">About Leigh Spencer</h2>
      <p class="compass__p">
        I’ve been reading tarot and oracle cards for over 40 years.
      </p>
      <p class="compass__p">
        Before that, I spent 30 years as a journalist, broadcaster, and editor, trained to observe, interpret, and communicate clearly.
      </p>
      <p class="compass__p">
        COMPASS is built from real reading experience, and from seeing exactly where readers lose trust in themselves.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="compass__section">
      <h2 class="compass__h2">Enrollment</h2>
      <ul class="compass__list">
        <li>Limited to 6 participants</li>
        <li>Minimum 2 participants to run</li>
        <li>Live only, not replay-based delivery</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="compass__p">
        You are asked to apply because fit matters.
      </p>
      <p class="compass__p">
        This is a small live programme where direct feedback and outcome matter more than filling places.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="compass__section">
      <h2 class="compass__h2">Investment</h2>
      <p class="compass__p">
        NZD $497
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="compass__section">
      <h2 class="compass__h2">Apply</h2>
      <p class="compass__p">
        Send a short message with:
      </p>
      <ul class="compass__list">
        <li>Your experience level</li>
        <li>What’s not working in your readings</li>
        <li>Why you want to join</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="compass__p">
        If accepted, your place will be held for 48 hours.
      </p>
      <a class="compass__cta" href="mailto:hello@tidesofknowing.com">Apply Now</a>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .compass {
    padding: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 3.5rem) 0 clamp(3rem, 8vw, 5rem);
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .compass__h1 {
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.5vw, 2.65rem);
    line-height: 1.15;
    color: var(--mountain-water);
  }

  .compass__h2 {
    margin: 2.25rem 0 0.85rem;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.8vw, 1.65rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-style: normal;
    color: var(--mountain-water);
    line-height: 1.25;
  }

  .compass__section + .compass__section {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .compass__p {
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
    font-size: 1.06rem;
    line-height: 1.78;
  }

  .compass__list {
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    padding-left: 1.35rem;
    font-size: 1.06rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .compass__list li {
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .compass__cta {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 0.85rem 1.75rem;
    font-family: var(--font-nav);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--mountain-water);
    border: 2px solid var(--gold);
    border-radius: 2px;
    background: transparent;
  }

  .compass__cta:hover {
    background: rgba(198, 161, 74, 0.14);
    color: var(--mountain-water);
    border-color: var(--gold);
  }

  .compass__cta:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--gold);
    outline-offset: 4px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    .compass__h1 {
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 9vw, 2.45rem);
    }
  }
</style>

